summary: I want to make it clear
title: I want to make it clear
body:
I don’t have an issue with fans of Chris Evans(or any guy) fan girling over him with other women, in this case black women.

That’s normal many women do that with men and women they’d like to see together. (He’s been shipped with Brie Larson, Scarlett Johansson, RDJ, and most recently Danai Gurira) no big deal. 

In fact it’s not so much about Chris and more so about fans. My annoyance I guess is with people thirsting over real life situations and stretching the truth so they can fulfill some fantasy….but then like…. be deadass about it. 

It’s cringey and desperate.

summary: So it would appear that YouTube have finally updated their algorithm and have hidden all the Brie Larson hate videos when you...
body:
So it would appear that YouTube have finally updated their algorithm and have hidden all the Brie Larson hate videos when you search her name, so now you get genuine interviews etc. Also, on twitter, there is a whole ass thread of tweets of people supporting her since that (I don’t actually know if it’s true or not) comment she made about doubting herself came out. I hope this is a start to the end of the vile abuse she receives because she seems so genuine and soft.

If you don’t like her, fine. Everyone is entitled to an opinion, but openly bashing her and tagging her in abusive content online is not okay.
